    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.1947.37.25_1.jpg"/>
                <opener>
                    <address rend="letterhead">
                        <addrLine>The Avenue,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><placeName ref="#pl:Wimborne">Wimborne</placeName>, <placeName
                                ref="#pl:Dorset">Dorset</placeName></addrLine>
                    </address>

                    <dateline>
                        <date when="1882-03-21">March 21. 1882</date>
                    </dateline>

                    <salute>Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am requiring a freehold site on which to build a dwelling-house, &amp; the land
                    of the <persName ref="#ps:Ilchester5">Earl of Ilchester</persName> at <placeName
                        ref="#pl:StinsfordHill">Stinsford Hill</placeName>, near <placeName
                        ref="#pl:Dorchester">Dorchester</placeName> (where a board has for some time
                    been displayed stating that sites are to be let) would probably suit my purpose,
                    if such a plot <unclear>c</unclear>ould be
                        <del><unclear>purchase</unclear></del> disposed of out &amp; out to one
                    willing to make a beginning <add place="margin">there.</add>
                    <del rend="strikethrough">the property.</del> Should this be the case, can you
                    kindly inform me what would be the price per acre for a piece containing from 1
                    to 1Â½ acres?</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Faithfully yours</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="#ps:TH">Thomas Hardy</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>

                <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.1947.37.25_2.jpg"/>




            </div>
        </body>


